text: Franz Josef Kuhnle (27 April 1926 - 4 February 2021) was a German Roman Catholic auxiliary bishop. He became a priest in 1952. He was titular bishop of Sorres and as auxiliary bishop of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Rottenburg- Stuttgart, Germany from 1976 to 1990. Kuhnle died on 4 February 2021, aged 94.Franz Josef Kuhnle ==References== Category:1926 births Category:2021 deaths Category:German Roman Catholic bishops
